{"key":"processedPost-13182228","value":{"id":13182228,"first":13182132,"last":25095212,"when":1284263678,"utime":"09/12/10 06:54 AM","content":"No, it doesn't stunt growth of others or cause aborts.&nbsp; If the mature fruits are in a large cluster with others that are not ready, simply slice off the stems at the base with a sharp knife rather than picking.&nbsp; In fact, that's how I pick anyway.&nbsp; I don't like to twist the fruits off because it often damages the substrate, leaving a large wound.&nbsp; Leaving the stumps behind causes no problems.<br />RR","title":"Re: Does picking shrooms off cake stunt growth of others?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}